    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-03-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-03-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="116"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d116">
                <head>116. Memorandum for the Record<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d116fn1"
                        >Source: Central Intelligence Agency, Job 79-01025A, Box 151, Folder 6.
                        Secret. Prepared on March 15.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-03-14"
                        >March 14, 1954</date>.</dateline>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Conference Between the <gloss target="#t_DCI1">DCI</gloss> and Secretary
                        of State on 14 March 1954</item>
                </list>
                <p>1. Mr. <persName corresp="#p_WFHSW1">Wisner</persName> informed Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_BTPWD1">Barnes</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_KCJC1">Col.
                        King</persName> that at a meeting between the Director and the Secretary of
                    State yesterday the following decisions and/or actions were arrived at: <list>
                        <label>A.</label>
                        <item>The Secretary believes that there should be at an early date a review
                            of the <gloss target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss>
                            operation.</item>
                        <label>B.</label>
                        <item>The Secretary’s conclusion, after two weeks of observation at the
                            Caracas Conference, is that he sees no reason to change the tempo of
                                <gloss target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss>, but “don’t get
                            caught”.</item>
                        <label>C.</label>
                        <item>Will we give careful thought and study to the establishment of an
                            overt liberation committee consisting of refugees from Guatemala who are
                            not actively engaged or tied into <gloss target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1"
                                >PBSUCCESS</gloss>. The objectives are two: 1. To divert attention
                            from covert activities; 2. To use as a sounding board for propaganda.
                            The danger of producing confusion is realized. This is a request for
                            study, not an instruction to set up a new committee. The study should
                            include location of already active overt liberation committees, the
                            existence of any prominent Guatemalans in exile who are not members of
                            such committees, the most suitable country in which to set up such a
                            committee. Mr. <persName corresp="#p_WFHSW1">Wisner</persName> suggests
                            consideration of a notional committee. Action: [<hi rend="italic">name
                                not declassified</hi>].</item>
                        <label>D.</label>
                        <item>
                            <persName corresp="#p_TGG1">Toriello</persName>. The Secretary gained
                            the impression from his observation of <persName corresp="#p_TGG1"
                                >Toriello</persName> during the Caracas Conference that <persName
                                corresp="#p_TGG1">Toriello</persName> may be an opportunist and a
                            possible subject for defection. We are requested to prepare a memo for
                            the <gloss target="#t_DDP1">DD/P</gloss> containing what is immediately
                            available of background information on <persName corresp="#p_TGG1"
                                >Toriello</persName>. In this should be included whatever
                            information [<hi rend="italic">name not declassified</hi>] and [<hi
                                rend="italic">name not declassified</hi>] may have. A thorough
                            study, including CE aspects, is to be immediately initiated. <hi
                                rend="italic">Action:</hi>
                            <persName corresp="#p_EJD1">Esterline</persName>.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>[Omitted here is a paragraph unrelated to Guatemala.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_KCJC1">
                            <hi rend="strong">J.C. King</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chief, <gloss target="#t_WH1">WH</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
